in desperation now, wee must stand up now and participate in the democratic process at the end of which we will surely have a leader that will take us out of the mess in which we had been waddling upside for too long.

Sierra Leone, our beloved country, is now at a critical juncture posing a great challenge to us not to allow would- be-violators hinder us from living up to our responsibility by interfering in our collective right to free and transparent elections come March 7, 2007.

Therefore it is high time we get rid off those draconically and ruthless political contenders that thrive in violence during, before, and after the elections and cry foul in the event of their defeat or eventual removal from office. The Gloria Bayoh, Adama Kamara Kamara Assesment, and Ferguson cases must never happen because none of those dead people are back from the grave to take any credit for their untimely death during the brutal reign of the perverse in sierra Leone politics. Notwithstanding, their memory lives among us as we join the unconditional call to display our images throughout the country with a total respect and understanding of information submitted to the police and court system of our country.
